pull_request.title: Fixing OpenSSL SHA2 incremental API integration
pull_request.body:
Possibly fixes #1452. Fixes issues in #1420.

- Corrects SHA2 API documentation
- Checks all SHA2 OpenSSL API return values
- Fixes SHA384 and SHA512 incremental API implementations
- Corrects testing for these APIs
- Enhances test vectors to avoid re-occurrence of problem

* [yes] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [no] Does this PR change the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming? Does this PR otherwise change an API? (If so, PRs in [oqs-provider](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider), [OQS-OpenSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl), [OQS-BoringSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/boringssl), and [OQS-OpenSSH](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssh) will also need to be ready for review and merge by the time this is merged.)

review.body:
Apologies for the long silence on our side :-( and Thanks very much again for this PR -- particularly for the update to OpenSSL3/removing the dependency on oqs-openssl111!

In general, I'm happy with this PR, but when running it locally, the build failed, so CI will also fail :-( So, can I ask you to re-run the build along the lines of what the CI logic does and update the code as necessary? I'm particularly concerned about the hard-coded library version copies (see single comment ). For the actual commands that need to succeed for CI see https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-demos/blob/9a9b35fc28875e1fbe3ec1b6e6a8d4f0ca93b633/.circleci/config.yml#L406-L414)? In addition/alternatively, please consider activating a CircleCI account to run the CI under your account ID: We'd then be sure everything is OK prior to merge. If you don't like CircleCI, please consider using GitHub CI instead.

I reviewed the updates in oqs-template and they seem fine; I am assuming the rest is all autogenerated.

If we change the SPHINCS+-SHA256-xxx names as in https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/pull/1420#issuecomment-1545768142 then this will have to be revisited however.

pull_request.title: OID update for Sphincs, Dilithium, Kyber
pull_request.body:
This assigns new (O)IDs for all remaining Sphincs+ algorithms and removes Kyber90s and DilithiumAES variants. This may be merged when https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/pull/1420 lands. 

Given how many algorithms this removes we can enable some more of the remaining Sphincs algs if we want. Proposals/requests welcome.
